3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with data compression and quantization, which are important topics in multimedia applications. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the relevance of the proposed quantization scheme in the context of wireless networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a structured class of quantizers and discusses their performance in terms of asymptotics.
